<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1165039564320">
<term>improper integral</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1165039564326">an integral over an infinite interval or an integral of a function containing an infinite discontinuity on the interval; an improper integral is defined in terms of a limit. The improper integral converges if this limit is a finite real number; otherwise, the improper integral diverges</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
